## Required `npm run build` environment

Every variable in the **`npm run build`** **`env`** block is **required** for release builds. **Do not** describe them as optional in workflow comments, CONTRIBUTING, or README—maintainers **must** define the matching **GitHub repository variables** (and map them in YAML).

| Workflow `env` key              | Repository variable              | Purpose                                      |
| ------------------------------- | -------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| **`ORG_URL`**                   | **`DOMAIN_NAME`**                | Organization site URL / TheMusicTreeByline   |
| **`ORG_SPONSOR_BUTTON_URL`**    | **`ORG_SPONSOR_BUTTON_URL`**     | **`BtmtSponsorButton`** iframe `src`; **`SponsorSocialLink`** default |
| **`ORG_GITHUB_URL`**            | **`ORG_GITHUB_URL`**             | **`GithubSocialLink`** default (playground)  |
| **`ORG_PYPI_URL`**              | **`ORG_PYPI_URL`**               | **`PypiSocialLink`** default (playground)    |
| **`ORG_LINKEDIN_URL`**          | **`ORG_LINKEDIN_URL`**           | **`LinkedInSocialLink`** default (playground)|
| **`ORG_X_URL`**                 | **`ORG_X_URL`**                  | **`XSocialLink`** default (playground)       |
| **`ORG_MASTODON_URL`**          | **`ORG_MASTODON_URL`**           | **`MastodonSocialLink`** default (playground)|
| **`ORG_YOUTUBE_URL`**           | **`ORG_YOUTUBE_URL`**            | **`YouTubeSocialLink`** default (playground) |
| **`CONTACT_EMAIL`**             | **`CONTACT_EMAIL`**              | **`EmailSocialLink`** default (**mailto:**)  |

Local **`npm run build`** / **`npm run dev`**: **`scripts/assert-org-url.mjs`** merges **`playground/.env`** with **`process.env`** (shell wins), then requires every key above. **`ORG_SPONSOR_BUTTON_URL`** and all **`http(s)`** URLs except **`ORG_LINKEDIN_URL`** must be absolute **`https://`** (or **`http://`**). **`ORG_LINKEDIN_URL`** may omit the scheme (normalized in **`Social*Link`**). **`CONTACT_EMAIL`** must look like a valid email.

Adding a new inlined-at-build env var: extend **`assert-org-url.mjs`**, **`tsup.config.ts`** **`define`**, **`publish.yml`** **`env`**, **`playground/.env.example`**, **`.github/workflows/vercel-playground-env.yml`** **`env`**, **`scripts/sync-vercel-playground-env.mjs`** **`KEYS`**, and maintainer docs in the same change.

## Vercel playground env sync

**`vercel-playground-env.yml`** runs only on **`workflow_dispatch`** (manual). It pushes the same repository variables to the Vercel project used for **`playground/`** (targets **production**, **preview**, and **development**). **`scripts/sync-vercel-playground-env.mjs`** requires every playground key and fails if any value is empty.

| Item | Source |
| ---- | ------ |
| **`VERCEL_TOKEN`** | Repository **secret** |
| **`VERCEL_PROJECT_ID`** | Repository **variable** |
| **`VERCEL_TEAM_ID`** | Optional repository **variable** (omit for personal-scope projects; set when the project is under a Vercel team) |
| Playground keys (`DOMAIN_NAME` → **`ORG_URL`**, plus the same names as **`publish.yml`**) | Repository **variables** — same table as above |
